trans-unit.source: A collection of <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.RuleSettings"></xref> objects.
This class cannot be inherited.
<xref:System.Web.Configuration.RuleSettings> objects are used to define event rules.
Initializes a new instance of the <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.RuleSettingsCollection"></xref> class.

The <xref:System.Web.Configuration.HealthMonitoringSection.EventMappings%2A> property of the <xref:System.Web.Configuration.HealthMonitoringSection> class always contains an instance of the <xref:System.Web.Configuration.RuleSettingsCollection>.
Use this instance, rather than creating a new instance of the class.
Adds a <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.RuleSettings"></xref> object to the collection.
The collection must not already contain a <xref:System.Web.Configuration.RuleSettings> object with the same name.
A <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.RuleSettings"></xref> object to add to the collection.
The <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.RuleSettings"></xref> object to add already exists in the collection or the collection is read-only.
Removes all <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.RuleSettings"></xref> objects from the collection.
This method inserts a `clear` directive into the appropriate section of the configuration file to clear all references to elements defined in a higher-level configuration file.
All elements defined in the appropriate section of the current configuration file are removed.
Returns `true` if the collection contains a <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.RuleSettings"></xref> object with the specified name.
Returns `false` if the specified name does not exist.
The name of a <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.RuleSettings"></xref> object in the collection.
`true` if the collection contains a <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.RuleSettings"></xref> object with the specified name; otherwise, `false`.
Finds the index of a <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.RuleSettings"></xref> object in the collection with the specified name.
Returns -1 if a <xref:System.Web.Configuration.RuleSettings> object with the specified name is not in the collection.
The name of a <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.RuleSettings"></xref> object in the collection.
The index of a <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.RuleSettings"></xref> object in the collection with the specified name.
Adds the specified <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.RuleSettings"></xref> object to the specified index point in the collection.
If the index parameter equals the number of items in the collection, then the entry is appended to the end of the collection.
A valid index of a <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.RuleSettings"></xref> object in the collection.
The <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.RuleSettings"></xref> object to insert into the collection.
The <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.RuleSettings"></xref> object to add already exists in the collection, the index is invalid, or the collection is read only.
Gets the <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.RuleSettings"></xref> object at the specified numeric index.
A <xref:System.Web.Configuration.RuleSettings> object at the specified index must exist.
The index of a <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.RuleSettings"></xref> object in the collection.
The <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.RuleSettings"></xref> object at the specified index.
Index is out of range.
Gets the <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.RuleSettings"></xref> object based on the specified key in the collection.
The name of the <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.RuleSettings"></xref> object contained in the collection.
A <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.RuleSettings"></xref> object.
Removes a <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.RuleSettings"></xref> object from the collection.
This method inserts a `remove` element into the appropriate section of the configuration file for any element defined in a higher-level configuration file.
If the element is defined in the appropriate section of the current configuration file, its entry is removed from the configuration file.
The object to remove must exist in the collection.
The name of a <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.RuleSettings"></xref> object in the collection.
There is no <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.RuleSettings"></xref> object with the specified key in the collection, the element has already been removed, or the collection is read-only.
Removes a <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.RuleSettings"></xref> object at the specified index location from the collection.
This method inserts a `remove` element into the appropriate section of the configuration file for any element defined in a higher-level configuration file.
If the element is defined in the appropriate section of the current configuration file, its entry is removed from the configuration file.
The object to remove must exist in the collection.
A valid index of a <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.RuleSettings"></xref> object in the collection.
There is no <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.RuleSettings"></xref> object at the specified index in the collection, the element has already been removed, or the collection is read-only.
